Ahead of the Easter celebration, the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, NSCDC Delta state command has deployed 2,418 personnel to secure lives and government infrastructures in the state. The State Commandant of the NSCDC, Akinsanya I A, who approved the deployment noted that the peace being enjoyed in the State should not be taken for granted hence the Command’s personnel will be complementing other security agencies in providing watertight security coverage before, during and after the celebration. This was contained in a statement signed by NSCDC Public Relations Officer, DSC Emeka Peters. The NSCDC image maker said the deployment is “In line with the core mandate of the NSCDC in the protection of lives and properties. He stressed the readiness of the Commandant led administration in maintaining peace and order in the State. The NSCDC boss maintained that the personnel were drafted from the Tactical Squad, the Anti-Vandal Unit, the Agro-Rangers, Counter Terrorism Unit CTU, the Rapid Respond Unit, Operations Dept, the Snipper Combatant (Female Squad) and the Department of Intelligence and Investigation (DII). He directed all Area Commanders, Divisional Officers, Component Commanders and Squadron Leaders to supervise and monitor the deployed officers and ensure they operate within the extant laws and discharge their duty with professionalism in line with international best practices.